# 🧑‍💼 Employee Management System (Tkinter + MySQL)

A desktop-based **Employee Management System** built using **Python Tkinter** for the GUI and **MySQL** for the database.  
This project helps manage employee records with features like **add, update, delete, search, and generate reports**.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Add new employees with details (ID, Name, Age, Salary, Department, etc.)
- Update employee records easily
- Delete employees
- Search and view employee details
- Data stored securely in **MySQL database**
- Clean and interactive **Tkinter GUI**
- Export employee details to **PDF reports** (with charts)
- Dropdown options for quick actions

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Python** (Tkinter for GUI)
- **MySQL** (Database)
- **ReportLab / Matplotlib** (PDF & charts)
- **Pillow** (for image/logo support in reports)

---

## 📂 Project Structure

EmployeeManagement/
│── main.py # Main Tkinter app
│── report.py # Report generation (PDF & charts)
│── db_connection.py # MySQL connection setup
│── requirements.txt # Dependencies
│── assets/ # (Optional: logo, icons, etc.)
│── README.md # Project documentation

---

## ⚡ Installation & Setup

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/employee-management-tkinter.git
   cd employee-management-tkinter
   ```

pip install -r requirements.txt

Setup MySQL database:

Create a database (e.g., employee_management)

Import tables using:
CREATE DATABASE employee_management;
USE employee_management;
Run the project:
python main.py

